<paragraph id="8BB5993BC146A67BFF0CA45CFEF460C0" blockId="28.[212,1171,1006,1229]" pageId="28" pageNumber="1933">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0AE2B8C146A67BFE93A45FFE076020" authorityName="Santos et Aguiar" authorityYear="2014" box="[331,434,1045,1069]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Loxopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="1933" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duckei">
<emphasis id="B97E4529C146A67BFE93A45FFE076020" box="[331,434,1045,1069]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="1933">L. duckei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it can be differentiated by the orbital band complete (versus widely interrupted and dorsal portion of gena); subalar ridge moderately wide, elliptic (versus narrow, dash-like), and bright yellow (versus ferruginous or whitish); transverse furrow at base of propodeum with distinct striae (versus almost indistinct); juxtacoxal carina present (versus absent); and T1 anteriorly orange (versus blackish).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
